==Description==

The [[Image:Curves_MixedCurve.svg|24px]] '''Curves MixedCurve''' tool creates a 3D intersection curve, a Mixed_curve object, of two projected curves. Optionally it can connect each source curve and the intersection curve with a ruled surface.

==Usage==

# Select two curves.
# There are several ways to invoke the tool:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:Curves_MixedCurve.svg|16px]] [[Curves_MixedCurve|Mixed curve]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|Curves → [[Image:Curves_MixedCurve.svg|16px]] Mixed curve}} option from the menu.
# A '''Mixed_Curve''' object is created.
# In the [[Property_View|Property View]] edit the {{PropertyData|Direction1}} and {{PropertyData|Direction2}} properties to set the projection directions.<br>This is optional if both selected curves were made with the [[Image:Workbench_Sketcher.svg|16px]] [[Sketcher_Workbench|Sketcher Workbench]].

==Notes==

* Projection directions are automatically detected if possible. In case of [[Sketcher_Workbench|Sketcher]] curves, the normal of the sketch plane is used.
* The {{PropertyData|Direction1}} and {{PropertyData|Direction2}} properties override automatically detected directions. It is mandatory to enter values manually if it is not possible to detect a direction automatically.

==Properties==

See also: [[Property_View|Property View]].

A '''Mixed_Curve''' object is derived from a [[Part_Feature|Part Feature]] object and inherits all its properties. It also has the following additional properties:

===Data===

{{TitleProperty|Mixed Curve}}

* {{PropertyData|Direction1|Vector}}: Projection direction of the shape in the {{PropertyData|Shape1}} property. If vector is null the shape's placement is used.
* {{PropertyData|Direction2|Vector}}: Projection direction of the shape in the {{PropertyData|Shape2}} property. If vector is null the shape's placement is used.
* {{PropertyData|Fill Face1|Bool}}: If {{True}} ruled surfaces are created between the shape in the {{PropertyData|Shape1}} property and the resulting Mixed_Curve. (default is {{False}})
* {{PropertyData|Fill Face2|Bool}}: If {{True}} ruled surfaces are created between the shape in the {{PropertyData|Shape2}} property and the resulting Mixed_Curve. (default is {{False}})
* {{PropertyData|Shape1|Link}}: Link to the first selected shape.
* {{PropertyData|Shape2|Link}}: Link to the second selected shape.

{{TitleProperty|Shape Approximation}}

* {{PropertyData|Active|Bool}}: Use Approximation.
* {{PropertyData|Approx Tolerance|Float}}: Approximation tolerance.
* {{PropertyData|Continuity|Enumeration}}: Desired continuity of the curves. Options: {{Value|C0}}, {{Value|C1}}, {{Value|G1}}, {{Value|C2}}, {{Value|G2}}, {{Value|C3}} (default), {{Value|CN}}
* {{PropertyData|Degree Max|Integer}}: Maximum degree of the curve. (default is {{Value|5}})
* {{PropertyData|Degree Min|Integer}}: Minimum degree of the curve. (default is {{Value|3}})
* {{PropertyData|Extension Proxy|PythonObject}}: Proxy object of the approximation extension.
* {{PropertyData|Parametrization|Enumeration}}: Parametrization type.
** {{Value|ChordLength}}:
** {{Value|Centripetal}}:
** {{Value|Uniform}}:
* {{PropertyData|Samples|Integer}}: Number of samples.


